              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": " (Thomson Reuters Foundation) — ",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 2,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "“Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies are created or ‘mined’ by high-powered computers competing to solve complex mathematical puzzles. It is a process that guzzles energy and fuels planet-heating emissions, unless the machines run on power from renewable sources. Meanwhile, there is debate around how effectively such operations can replace jobs lost when coal mines and other fossil fuel businesses shut.”",
